actices related to the design, facilitation, direction and assessment of blended learning experiences, Teaching in Blended Learning Environments addresses the growing demand for improved teaching in higher education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEducation, Higher -- Computer-assisted instruction. 7aEDUCATION / Distance, Open & Online Education.2bisacsh  aEducation.  aEducational technology.  aOnline learning.  aPedagogy.1 aCleveland-Innes, Martha, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGarrison, D. Randy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356487/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles